Gunmen suspected to be bandits on Thursday went on a rampage in the Federal Capital Territory (FCT), setting ablaze two tractors and abducting no fewer than 22 farmers.⁣
⁣
The incident occurred at Rafin-Daji community in Gurdi Ward of Abaji Area Council of Abuja.⁣
⁣
A farmer who escaped abduction told newsmen that the incident happened around 2:00 p.m on Thursday when the bandits wielding AK-47 rifles attacked the farmers that were tilling their land in the Rafin-Daji community, which shares a boundary with a community in Niger State.⁣
⁣
According to him, 13 persons from the same family were among the 22 abducted.⁣
The District Head of Gurdi Chiefdom, Alhaji Bala Mohammed, confirmed the abduction of the farmers and burning of tractors but said he was yet to ascertain the number of the people abducted.⁣
⁣
The district head who lamented that his people were under siege as bandits usually invaded his community through Niger State said he had reported the latest kidnap incident to the police and the authorities of the Abaji Area Council.⁣
⁣

Bandits assassinate lecturer at Zamfara State's Abdu Gusau Polytechnic, after duping his family into paying a massive ransom

According to reports, the deceased, Sanusi Halilu Kaura, was taken more than a month ago while traveling to Abuja for the NYSC mobilization of polytechnic students on the Kaduna-Abuja route.

The terrorists were alleged to have sought a five million naira ransom for the academician's release, which was paid by his family.

According to a family source who talked with newsmen, the bandits were given a five million naira ransom on Tuesday in a jungle near several communities along the Kaduna-Zaria route in Kaduna State.

He claimed that the bandits informed the family that Kaura had been slain shortly afterwards. According to reports, the finding suggests that the terrorists murdered Kaura long ago, even as discussions for his release were ongoing.

🎞 Les Lyonnais de @oliviermarchalofficiel sorti en 2011 avec Gérard Lanvin, Tchéky Karyo et Daniel Duval.

Autre film sur le grand banditisme, cette fois dans la belle ville de Lyon. 
Le gang des Lyonnais sévit entre 1967 et 1977. Il était constitué d'un noyau dur de 8 individus et dont le meneur s'appelait Monmon. Leur popularité provenait d'une rigueur quasi militaire dans leurs interventions et une très grande discrétion. Ils sont à l'origine de plusieurs braquages dont l'un qui reste le plus célèbre, celui de l'Hôtel des Postes de Strasbourg.

Les 3 acteurs principaux, on ne les présente plus. Ils sont devenus des icônes du cinéma français. Lanvin toujours aussi charismatique et qui campe à la perfection le rôle du parrain gitan, Karyo que l'on retrouve avec grand plaisir dans le rôle d'un truand et Duval, grande figure cinématographique française, 44 ans de carrière et 70 films...bref, sans commentaires ! 😄

En tant que fan de ce genre de films, j'ai adoré l'ambiance gitane que l'on retrouve assez peu dans le grand banditisme au cinéma, la bande son est plutôt sympa on y retrouve des titres des années 60 et 70...forcément, le rythme du film nous tient en haleine jusqu'à la dernière seconde et Lanvin crève littéralement l'écran...oui j'aime beaucoup Gérard 😆

Encore une fois, ce n'est pas un film pour les hémophiles hein ! 😉

The infamous California bandit Joaquin Murrieta is considered a hero by many.

Originally from Sonora, Mexico, Murrieta flocked to California in 1849 during the great gold rush where he supposedly was the victim of great injustice.

Legend states Joaquin's gold claim was stolen, his brother lynched, and he himself tied up, horsewhipped, and forced to watch his wife's rape. A rape so vicious she later died.

This atrocity caused Murrieta to lash out, seeking revenge. He began targeting the white gold miners, robbing and killing and - at the same time - protecting his fellow immigrants.

The legend of Joaquin Murrieta is said to be the inspired behind Zorro and even Batman! But how true is it?

Was Joaquin really a hero? Or simply just another blood thirsty criminal, preying on the weak?

And where's his gold at!?

Find out the whole story on the most recent episode of The Wild West Extravaganza! Link in bio or available wherever you listen to podcasts!

I know things didn't end the way we wanted it to but special thanks to QB1 Jordan Ta'amu for a memorable Tampa Bay Bandits season. Jordans been the 808 homie since day one and it was inspiring to see a fellow Hawai'i born player get his chance and make the most out of an amazing opportunity. He's a special quarterback that I hope someday gets a chance in the NFL. Sure he made his mistakes but given the situation he was in, I think he did what he could. Jordan had an O-line that struggled to protect him. He had no run game. His receivers would drop crucial balls and couldn't consistently create separation. His offensive playcalling/coach was hella sus. Not to mention the frequent shots he would take from opposing defenses. Despite all the noise, Jordan lead the USFL in passing yards, passing touchdowns, and was the USFL scoring leader. That's pretty impressive for a guy who didn't have the best help in the world. Idc what anyone says I'm proud of @jordan_taamu10. Thank you for being my quarterback and for being the bright spot in a lackluster offense.

Nineteen kidnapped Zamfara wedding guests have been liberated and are on their way to Gusau, the state capital.

Ashiru Zurmi, Secretary of the Zamfara State Communication Union, told media in Gusau on Thursday.

"I can affirm that our members regained their freedom today (Thursday)." "They're on their way to Gusau right now," he said.

He did not say whether the N145 million ransom sought by the kidnappers was paid.

The victims were kidnapped on June 11 while coming from the wedding of one of their members in Sokoto state at Dogon Awo, a border town between Sokoto and Zamfara states.

And there they are. Bandits, thieves, whatever you wanna call them. Though it looks like some bandits were here already when our thieves came in. The bandits were mining illegally, the thieves... well, they stole a painting, obviously.

Anyway, they attacked us, so we dealt with them. And then we found this tiny room. Really, the ceiling is so low, I almost bumped my head. No, Tharaêl couldn't stand upright in it.

We also found the stolen painting in this room (yes, it's just one, Andrasta clarified that before we left). And... it started talking to us.

Okay, so. Allegedly Andrasta is trapping the souls of her customers in her portraits of them. Or part of their soul, or something. The guy in this painting said he and his companion (who might be dead now, sorry) are some sort of witch hunter who set out to stop Andrasta, one way or the other.

The painting asked us to help him get revenge and escape the painting. We'll see, first I want to hear what Andrasta has to say. So, tomorrow we'll be heading back to her, carrying this blocky thing with us. Fun times.

But first we'll clean up a bit here, get rid of the corpses, and then make ourselves comfortable for the night. It's too late to head back now.

An unspecified number of residents were on Thursday at Rahamawa and Shagari low-cost housing estates of Katsina State abducted by bandits.

A source told DAILY POST that the attackers came in broad daylight, trekking with the victims to the place they packed their motorcycles.

According to the source, the bandits came around 6:15 am on Thursday and the people saw them moving with their captives and learned that they are from the Rahamawa area of Katsina.

He added, “Our people said they have seen about 13 to 15 attackers moving in a haste with the people they kidnapped.”

He explained that there was an exchange of gunfire with security agents to disperse the attackers and rescue the victims, stressing that he was not sure whether all the captives were rescued or not.

He added that security agents were in hot pursuit of the attackers to rescue the victims.

According to him, they had prior information of their movement and laid ambush on their route with other security agents, saying that to their surprise, they could not detect where they laid low.

He explained that they left the area around 4 am only to discover that the bandits attacked communities around Shagari Low-cost, saying that a team of soldiers, police, and vigilantes are trailing them including a helicopter from the Nigerian Air Force.

Muhammadu Buhari on Wednesday decried the recent spate of church attacks in the country, describing the development as unacceptable. ⁣
⁣
“From the tragedy in Owo two weeks ago that shook our nation to its core, to the killings and kidnappings just this weekend in Kaduna State, it is clear that there is a design by wicked people to put the country under religious stress,” he said.⁣
⁣
According to President Buhari, “our religious freedom and diversity are what makes Nigeria great. It is this diversity that gives Nigeria its strength. That is why Nigeria’s enemies seek to destroy it, by pitting us against one another.⁣
⁣
“We will not let them. The nation will not be distracted or divided by these obviously planned and politically motivated criminal outrages.”⁣
⁣

⁣

President Muhammadu Buhari on Wednesday decried the recent spate of church attacks in the country, describing the development as unacceptable. ⁣
⁣
“From the tragedy in Owo two weeks ago that shook our nation to its core, to the killings and kidnappings just this weekend in Kaduna State, it is clear that there is a design by wicked people to put the country under religious stress,” he said.⁣
⁣
According to President Buhari, “our religious freedom and diversity are what makes Nigeria great. It is this diversity that gives Nigeria its strength. That is why Nigeria’s enemies seek to destroy it, by pitting us against one another.⁣
⁣
“We will not let them. The nation will not be distracted or divided by these obviously planned and politically motivated criminal outrages.”⁣
⁣

Ondo State Police Command stated on Wednesday that 14 suspected offenders were apprehended throughout the state.

Ojo Rotimi, Tosin Omoniyi, Jimoh Dele, Uwanfor Destiny, Babajide Moses, Tope Gbenga, John Simeon, Akinniranye Blessing, Jude Stephen, and Iranlowo Ayomide are among the accused.

Omoniyi was allegedly apprehended while attempting to rape a lady after robbing her family of goods in their home in the Idanre village of the state's Idanre Local Government Area.

According to authorities, the suspect broke into the couple's flat through the window about 1:00 a.m. and stole their money and other belongings.

Seven gunmen attacked Orin Ekiti in the Ido/Osi Council Area of Ekiti State and abducted a retired top public official named Bamisaye, who was working in his farm.

According to sources, the farm where the tragedy happened was between Ero Dam and the Ekiti State agricultural community at Orin Ekiti.

According to a source, the development has caused tension and panic in the town, with residents concerned about their safety.

"The seven gunmen had previously attacked one individual named Ojo near the farm where Bamisaye was taken," he claimed.

"When queried about the location of the white guys working at the agricultural community, Ojo stated that he didn't know."
"They told him to lie down face down. They raided his neighboring parked car and stole the N4,500 they discovered inside. "They fired a shot and panicked the surrounding area before finding Bamisaye and whisking him away," the person added.

According to the Corps Commandant of the Ekiti State Amotekun Corps, operatives of the corps as well as individuals from the state's security agencies began working on the development as soon as they received the information.

When contacted for confirmation, the Police Public Relations Officer, Ekiti State Command, Sunday Abutu, did not answer.

Aliyu Hammanseyo, a middle-aged resident of Adamawa State's Mubi North Local Government Area, has been remanded in custody after reportedly killing his companion with a knife over N1,500.

Hammanseyo, who was charged at Yola's Chief Magistrate's Court, was remanded in custody for the alleged crime.

According to the charge sheet read by the police prosecutor, ASP Francis Audu, before Magistrate Muhammed Abubakar, Hammanseyo fatally stabbed Bilham Babangida on June 7, 2022, using a knife.

Additionally, he claimed that under questioning, the defendant acknowledged to stabbing Babangida in the chest.

Soldiers from the 13 Brigade of the Nigerian Army (NA) have stopped a Toyota Camry with the license plate JAL 492 AA that was carrying military gear and munitions.

Brigadier General Onyema Nwachukwu, the director of army public relations, stated in a statement that the vehicle was stopped on Tuesday while traveling from Obudu in Cross River State to Utanga village.

The following is an excerpt from the statement: "Troops stationed at Forward Operating Base, Amana, tried to halt the car at their checkpoint, but the driver sped away. The military had to open fire on the vehicle's tyres in order to immobilize it due to the drivers' resistance.

"A comprehensive examination of the van revealed it was transporting 121 dynamite liquid, 72 Improvised Explosive Device (IED) charges, and 200 NATO 7.62 mm bullets and 82 unique 7.62 mm rounds were used.

In addition, Gen Nwachukwu revealed that among the goods found in the car were military uniforms and equipment.

In order to stop the spread of insecurity across the nation, he pleaded with the public to continue providing them with reliable information.

HITTIN' THE TRAIL IN THE WILD WEST: SILI-CON CARNE AND TEDDITO- 
The voluptuous Sili-con Carne is the cunning, resourceful, and daring leader of the Banditos who are terrorizing the settlers in the area, but for what purpose? 
 
Not even Sili-con Carne's most faithful and trusted lieutenant, the dour Teddito, knows.  Though Teddito would never question his head-strong leader, he inadvertently learns that Sili-con Carne is being used as a pawn by a master manipulator in a plot that would be disastrous for the Settlers and the Banditos as well. 
 
Teddito does not know which way to turn, until he remembers an old saying, "The enemy of my enemy is my friend!" The Master Manipulator may be up against more than he bargained for!

Usman Alkali Baba, the Inspector-General of Police, has sent out more police officers to increase security along the Abuja-Kaduna Highway to combat kidnapping and banditry.

The police commissioner in charge of the Police Mobile Force, CP Matthew Akinyoshola, addressed the staff on Wednesday at the Force Headquarters just before their deployment and advised the mobile policemen to be watchful and attentive at all times in their respective jurisdictions.

He issued a warning to the police, advising them to carry out their duty with civility and firmness while taking swift action against anyone who poses a threat to the country's peace and security.

Numerous bandit attacks on the Abuja-Kaduna route have resulted in the killing and maiming of innocent motorists as well as the kidnapping of locals.

The robbers have continued to have a field day despite several guarantees from the Federal Government and the Kaduna State Government, despite the deployment of security personnel, including troops.

In the Kajuru Local Government Area of Kaduna State, bandits invaded four communities on Sunday and kidnapped no less than 36 individuals.

Residents in the area reported to security agents that the frequent attacks have hurt their ability to make a living because they can no longer travel to their crops without risking bandit attack or kidnapping.

They argued that the only way to improve the security situation was for the Federal Government to set up a military base in Kajuru.

Gunmen, who attacked Maranatha Baptist Church and St. Moses Catholic Church in Robuh, Ungwan Aku, Kajuru Local Council of Kaduna State, on Sunday, are demanding N100 million to free about 36 worshippers in their custody.⁣ ⁣ Kaduna State Commissioner for Internal Security and Home Affairs, Samuel Aruwan, had confirmed three persons were killed in the attack by the bandits, who reportedly stormed the communities on about 30 motorcycles.⁣ ⁣ The traditional leader of Angwan Fada at Robuh, who was a victim, Elisha Mari, disclosed to journalists yesterday that the abductors released him to go look for N100 million to secure the release of others.⁣ ⁣ He spoke to journalists when heads of security agencies and the Kaduna government delegation visited him, yesterday. Explaining that it took them about two hours to arrive at the bandits’ camp, he noted that he was freed because of his traditional title, but was asked to raise at least N100 million ransom before those in captivity would be freed.⁣ ⁣ A witness, Bashir Usman, told journalists that the three persons who were killed tried to repel the terrorists. A new title has arrived at #phil_nicholls_books

When I posted last week about the recent visit to the fantastic second-hand bookshop at Blickling Hall, I noted that I had found a book in the wrong section. The book in question was Bandits by Elmore Leonard, published by Penguin in 1987. 

I found this in General Fiction, when I think it really should have been shelved under Crime Fiction. This book takes me back to my job as a Bookseller at Heathrow Airport when I ran the Crime Fiction Section. Elmore Leonard was a staple author and someone I enjoyed reading.

The books I had were lost when I cut down the size of my collection, but here I am building it up again. Leonard is characterised by snappy dialogue and clever plots, which makes him a popular choice for films. I have not read Bandits before, but I have high hopes on the back of other books of his I have read. I am especially looking forward to basking in his characterization.

HITTIN' THE TRAIL IN THE WILD WEST: BARTON "BAR" NUNN- 
Barton (better known as "Bar") Nunn had been a friend and neighbor of Uncle Rollin Stone for many a year. 
 
Bar owned the largest spread in the territory, but he'd always been there for Rollin.  For many a year, they've weathered many a travail together. 
 
This current challenge had been no exception.  The attacks of the marauding Banditos had victimized many of the ranches in the territory, driving many families out of their homes.  Barton had said that even he had been hit, but all his resources had been to no avail against the Banditos. 
 
This is what faced Hacker and his posse (Pug, Dudley, Sagebrush and Running Moss) when they came riding in (though no coming battle could be more devastating than the one brewing between Pinata and Runny Moss for control of the kitchen). 
 
The "Big City" cynicism of Pug, however, sensed something disquieting about the apparent beneficence of Uncle Rollin's neighbor.  The Banditos seemed to be too slick, almost like they had someone helping them.  Pug hoped it was just his imagination, but planned to keep an eye open anyway.

Bandits have attacked intending pilgrims from Issa Local Government Area of Sokoto State who were on their way to the state capital for their onward journey to Saudi Arabia. 

However, the state government confirmed that the intending pilgrims were rescued unscathed.

This was contained in a statement issued by the Special Adviser, Media and Publicity to the state governor, Muhammad Bello, on Monday.

The statement quoted the state Commissioner for Information, Isah Bajini Galadanchi, saying the intending pilgrims, their relatives, and security men who were accompanying them to the hajj camp were held up by the bandits. 

“The intending pilgrims has already been received by government officials and is being processed for their onward journey to the Holy Land,” the statement maintained.

Suspected bandits have released from their captivity the head of Zira village in the Toro Local Government Area of Bauchi State, Yahya Abubakar, and his son, Habibu.

They were released on Tuesday morning and have been reunited with their family.

The PUNCH had reported that gunmen suspected to be bandits invaded and attacked Zira at about 2am on Saturday and kidnapped the village head and his son.

It was unclear if a ransom was paid by the family of the village head before they were released.

Gunmen, who attacked Maranatha Baptist Church and St. Moses Catholic Church in Robuh, Ungwan Aku, Kajuru Local Council of Kaduna State, on Sunday, are demanding N100 million to free about 36 worshippers in their custody.⁣
⁣
Kaduna State Commissioner for Internal Security and Home Affairs, Samuel Aruwan, had confirmed three persons were killed in the attack by the bandits, who reportedly stormed the communities on about 30 motorcycles.⁣
⁣
The traditional leader of Angwan Fada at Robuh, who was a victim, Elisha Mari, disclosed to journalists yesterday that the abductors released him to go look for N100 million to secure the release of others.⁣
⁣
He spoke to journalists when heads of security agencies and the Kaduna government delegation visited him, yesterday. Explaining that it took them about two hours to arrive at the bandits’ camp, he noted that he was freed because of his traditional title, but was asked to raise at least N100 million ransom before those in captivity would be freed.⁣
⁣
A witness, Bashir Usman, told journalists that the three persons who were killed tried to repel the terrorists. According to him, one woman sadly had one of her ears cut off by the terrorists.⁣

At least twenty-one intended Muslim pilgrims allegedly escaped death when bandit terrorists assaulted their caravan in Sokoto State on Monday

According to reports, the muslims were on their way to Sokoto from the state's Isa Local Government Area preparatory of their departure for the Holy Land on Tuesday when the gunmen ambushed their vehicle.

Security officers accompanying the Muslim victims, on the other hand, are said to have repulsed the gun-wielding terrorists and brought the murderous onslaught to a halt.

According to Malam Sirajo, a local of Isa town, the caravan was assaulted in Gundumi forest, but the intended pilgrims escaped unharmed, and some of them were transported back to Sarkin Gobir Isa's palace.

"They attacked their caravan, which was escorted by security personnel who were claimed to have engaged the robbers for many minutes."

Sirajo was cited saying, "We learned that some of the operatives had injuries, which I cannot verify."

Shehu Muhammad Dange, the Permanent Secretary of the Sokoto State Scholarship Board, said he couldn't confirm if anyone was kidnapped during the attack.

He did confirm, however, that there were 21 intending pilgrims from Isa, and that he was still awaiting information on their status.

When reached, ASP Ahmad Rufa'i, the acting Public Relations Officer of the Sokoto State Police Command, stated he was unaware about the attack.

The District Head of Panyam in Mangu Local Government Area of Plateau State, Adamu Derwam has been kidnapped by gunmen suspected to be terrorists.

The gunmen reportedly attacked Derwam’s residence at about 1,30am on Monday, shooting sporadically to scare away residents.

Moses Garuba, a village resident, said that the gunmen were around 20.

The attackers, numbering in the dozens and highly armed, encircled the district head's residence in Panyam just after midnight.

"Because his house was not fenced, some locals who noticed how it was encircled by strange persons used a communal bell to inform other members of the community."

However, as soon as the terrorists rang the bell, they began firing and eventually fled with the traditional ruler, leaving the town defenseless," he claimed.

DSP Alfred Alabo, a spokesman for the State Police Command, verified the event and said a tactical squad of police, military, vigilantes, and hunters had been dispatched to the region to rescue the paramount ruler.

Alabo, who emphasized that every attempt is being made to save the victim's life, urged members of the public to provide credible information to the police on how to track down the criminals.

The kidnapping of the district head is the latest in a string of kidnappings in the state aimed at traditional rulers and monks.

Gunmen attacked worshippers yesterday, June 19th 2022 at Maranatha Baptist Church and St Moses Catholic Church in Robuh, Ungwan Aku, and locals at Ungwan Fada, Ungwan Turawa and Ungwan Makama in Rubu General area of Kajuru local government in Kaduna State.

According to reports, the worshippers at St Moses Catholic church were attacked while rounding up their first mass leaving three worshipers dead and an unspecified number of persons kidnapped.

The Kaduna State government through the commissioner for internal and home affairs, Samuel Aruwabln said reports from security agencies had it that the bandits stormed the villages on motorcycles, beginning from Ungwan Fada, and moved into Ungwan Turawa, before Ungwan Makama and then Rubu.

“In Rubu village, the bandits attacked worshippers in the Maranatha Baptist Church and St. Moses Catholic Church.
“Three locals have been confirmed killed in the attacks. They are identified as Peter Madaki (ward head of Ungwan Fada), Elisha Ezekiel (resident of Ungwan Fada), Ali Zamani (youth leader of Rubu).

“Two persons were left injured in the attacks: one Aniro Mai, and a yet-unidentified woman. An unspecified number of locals were also kidnapped, according to the received reports.

“The bandits looted shops and carted away some valuables from the villages,” Aruwan said.

 He also mentioned that “Security patrols are being conducted in the general area as investigations are ongoing”.
